xyz.swatt.selenium

Class WebDriverWrapper

  • java.lang.Object
    • xyz.swatt.selenium.WebDriverWrapper
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    WebDriverTransitionalWrapper

    public class WebDriverWrapper
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable
    This class is a wrapper for the Selenium WebDriver class.

    It's purpose is to make common tasks easier and catch/fix common problems.

    All WebDriver interactions are Synchronized on the LOCK object. (The WebDriver / Web Browser can only do one thing at a time, just like a real person.) This allows Multi-Threading to be used with Selenium.

    Author:
    Brandon Dudek (BrandonDudek)

      • WebDriverWrapper

        public WebDriverWrapper(WebDriverWrapper.FirefoxBrowser _browser,
                        java.lang.String... _firefoxExtensionNames)
        Instantiates this WebDriverWrapper to use the given WebDriverWrapper.FirefoxBrowser.

        (Designed to work with Firefox version 56.0.2.)

        Notes:

        - Will look at the default install path for the Firefox app. (Can be overridden by setting firefoxOverridePath.)

        - The Window will be maximized.

        - Downloads will automatically start and the files will be saved to FireFox's default download location. (Stored in DEFAULT_DOWNLOAD_PATH.)

        Parameters:
        _browser - The WebDriverWrapper.FirefoxBrowser to use.
        _firefoxExtensionNames - A list of Firefox Add-On names. (Known names can be found in the WebDriverWrapper.FirefoxExtension enum.)
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If the given WebDriverWrapper.FirefoxBrowser is null.

        Or if firefoxOverridePath is used with undefined WebDriverWrapper.FirefoxBrowser.

      • WebDriverWrapper

        public WebDriverWrapper(WebDriverWrapper.IEBrowser _browser)
        Instantiates this WebDriverWrapper to use the given WebDriverWrapper.IEBrowser.

        Note: IE requires that the "Enable Protected Mode" Security Settings be set to the same value for all Security Zones. (see: http://automate-apps.com/unexpected-error-launching-internet-explorer-protected-mode-settings-are-not-the-same-for-all-zones/)

        Note: IE requires that the "Pop-up Blocking Level" to be set to "Low", in order to use the openNewWindow(boolean) functionality. (see: How to Turn Off Pop-Up Blocker in Internet Explorer )

        Note: The window will be maximized.

        Parameters:
        _browser - The Web WebDriverWrapper.IEBrowser to use.

        Note: IE 64 bit has slow typing, due to bug: Selenium Bug 5116

        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If the given WebDriverWrapper.IEBrowser is null.

      • killPreviousBrowserDriverProcesses

        public static void killPreviousBrowserDriverProcesses()
        This method will kill any Browser Driver processes that were started in previous runs.

        Should only be used at the beginning off execution (like in an @BeforeSuite method).

        Note: Will only execute on windows machine.

        Warning: This will kill any ECT-QED Tools' Selenium Drivers from other executions!

      • killUsedBrowserDriverProcesses

        public static void killUsedBrowserDriverProcesses()
        This method will kill all of the Browser Driver processes that were created during this run.

        Should only be used at the end off all execution (like in an @AfterSuite method).

        Note: Will only execute on windows machine.

      • tileWindows

        public static void tileWindows(boolean _zoomOut)
        Will tile all of the windows of all of the WebDriverWrappers that have been created and not quit. (If only 1 WebDriverWrapper is still active, then it will be maximized.)

        Note: For Chrome on a Mac, "maximise" may not fill the entire screen. It just expand the window to as large as it needs to be, to not have scroll bars (up to the size of the available screen space).

        Parameters:
        _zoomOut - If true, the windows will get zoomed out to the percentage that they are resided.

        Note: Firefox does not support the use of Control keys on the browser. (see: https://github.com/mozilla/geckodriver/issues/786.)

        Note: Chrome does not support the use of Control keys on the browser. (see: https://bugs.chromium.org/p/chromedriver/issues/detail?id=2265.)

      • tileWindows

        public static void tileWindows(java.util.concurrent.ConcurrentSkipListSet<WebDriverWrapper> _driverWrappers,
                               boolean _zoomOut)
        Will tile all of the given WebDrivers' active windows.

        (If only 1 WebDriver is given, it will be maximized.)

        Note: For Chrome on a Mac, "maximise" may not fill the entire screen. It just expand the window to as large as it needs to be, to not have scroll bars (up to the size of the available screen space).

        Parameters:
        _driverWrappers - The windows to tile, in a thread safe, unique collection. (see: ConcurrentSkipListSet)
        _zoomOut - If true, the windows will get zoomed out to the percentage that they are resided.

        Note: Firefox does not support the use of Control keys on the browser. (see: https://github.com/mozilla/geckodriver/issues/786.)

        Note: Chrome does not support the use of Control keys on the browser. (see: https://bugs.chromium.org/p/chromedriver/issues/detail?id=2265.)

        public WebElementWrapper getWebElementWrapper(org.openqa.selenium.By _by)

        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If the given By object is null.

        Or if the given Wait Time is negative.

        org.openqa.selenium.NoSuchElementException - If no WebElement is found, and if the _noElementExceptionMessage argument is not NULL.
        TooManyResultsException - If more than 1 WebElement is found.

      • getWebElementWrappers

        public java.util.List<WebElementWrapper> getWebElementWrappers(org.openqa.selenium.By _by)
        Waits maxElementLoadTime for at least one WebElement to exist and contain the correct visibility; then grabs all of the available WebElements.

        Note: Wait time can be a little longer (proportional to number of WebElements found), because of the time it takes to construct WebElementWrappers.

        Parameters:
        _by - How to search for the WebElements.
        Returns:
        A List of WebElementWrapper(s), if successful; or an empty List, if not.

      • getWebElementWrappers

        Waits maxElementLoadTime for at least one WebElement to exist and contain the correct visibility; then grabs all of the available WebElements.

        Parameters:

      • getWebElementWrappers

                                                               java.time.Duration _waitTime)

        Note: Wait time can be a little longer (proportional to number of WebElements found), because of the time it takes to construct WebElementWrappers.

        Parameters:

        _waitTime - How long to wait for the WebElement to exists and contain the correct visibility.

        Pass in 0 to only try to get the Elements once.

        Returns:
        A List of WebElementWrapper(s), if successful; or an empty List, if not.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If the given By object is null.

        Or if the given Wait Time is negative.

      • goToUrl

        public org.openqa.selenium.Alert goToUrl(java.lang.String _url)
        Loads a URL into the current Web Driver window and waits for the page to finish loading.

        Note: If an Alert is generated, it will be returned.

        Also: This can load a file into the browser, if the "URL" is in the format "file:ABSOLUTE_PATH".

        Parameters:
        _url - The URL to load.
        Returns:
        The Alert that was generated as a result of the navigation; or null, if there is no Alert.
        See Also:
        waitForPageLoad()

      • switchToFrame

        public void switchToFrame()
        Switches to the one and only visible Frame/IFrame on the page.

        Waits maxPageLoadTime for the Frame/IFrame to be available.

        Same as calling switchToFrame(By) and sending By.xpath( "//frame | //iframe" ).

        Throws:
        org.openqa.selenium.NoSuchElementException - If no Frame/IFrame is visible after maxPageLoadTime seconds of waiting.
        TooManyResultsException - If multiple Frames/IFrames are visible.

      • switchToFrame

        public void switchToFrame(org.openqa.selenium.By _by)
        Switches to the given Frame/IFrame.

        Waits maxPageLoadTime for the Frame/IFrame to be available.

        Parameters:
        _by - How to search for the Frame/IFrame.
        Throws:
        org.openqa.selenium.NoSuchElementException - If the Frame/IFrame cannot be found or is not visible after maxPageLoadTime seconds of waiting.
        TooManyResultsException - If the search returns multiple, visible Frames/IFrames.
        org.openqa.selenium.NoSuchFrameException - If the found Element is not a Frame/IFrame.
        See Also:
        getWebElementWrapper(By, Duration)

      • switchToWindow

        public void switchToWindow(int _index)
        Switches to the Window at the given index.

        Waiting up to maxPageLoadTime for the Window to load.

        Note: Window indexes are in the order that the windows were opened and only include currently opened windows.

        Parameters:
        _index - The 0-based index of the Window to switch to.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IndexOutOfBoundsException - If the given Index is less than 0 or greater than the number of open windows, after waiting maxPageLoadTime for the Window to load.

      • switchToWindow

        public void switchToWindow(java.lang.String _pageTitle)
        Switches to the window with the given Page Title.

        Waiting up to maxPageLoadTime for the Window to load.

        Note: Page Title is compared, ignoring the case, after trimming and normalization have been applied to the Title(s) and compare string.

        Parameters:
        _pageTitle - The Title of the Web Page's Browser Window to switch to.
        Throws:
        org.openqa.selenium.NotFoundException - If there is no Browser Window with the given Web Page Title.
        TooManyResultsException - If there is more than 1 Browser Window with the given Web Page Title.
